==English==
===Etymology===
Named from a character in [[w:George du Maurier|George du Maurier]]'s novel ''[[w:Trilby (novel)|Trilby]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/svɛŋˈgɑ:li/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑːli|-ɑːli]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# One who manipulates or controls another as by some mesmeric or sinister influence; especially with reference to coaches, mentors or industry moguls.
#:*'''2005''': She also offers a fascinating glimpse into a more innocent age before '''svengalis''' began colluding with marketing men and TV execs to promote talentless wannabes to overnight success. &mdash;''Hamilton Spectator'', October 15, 2005

